# ToDo List (Python)

## Overview
This is a simple command-line ToDo List application built with Python. Users can manage their tasks through an interactive menu, including adding, updating, deleting, and viewing tasks. This project was created to practice object-oriented programming (OOP), lists, loops, and user input handling.

## Features
- Add new tasks
- View all tasks
- Update existing tasks
- Delete tasks
- Interactive command-line menu

## Technologies
- Python 3

## How to Run
1. Clone this repository.
2. Open a terminal in the project folder.
3. Run:

```bash
python todo.py
```

## What I Learned
- Applying object-oriented programming
- Managing data using Python lists
- Handling user input in a command-line application

## Future Improvements
- Save tasks to a file so they remain after closing the program
- Delete and update tasks by task number instead of task name
- Add due dates and task priorities
- Improve error handling and input validation
